Package com.example.vybe

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddEditVibeActivity
    This Activity displays the screen for a user to add a vibe event, or edit an existing vibe event by adding or modifying the different vibe attributes
    AddEditVibeActivityTest
    Test class for MainActivity.
    ExampleInstrumentedTest
    Instrumented test, which will execute on an Android device.
    ExampleUnitTest
    Example local unit test, which will execute on the development machine (host).
    LogInActivity
    This activity gets the username and password and validates said fields with Firestore.
    MainActivity
    This Activity displays the screen for a user to log in.
    MainActivityTest
    Test class for MainActivity.
    MapFragment
    This fragment displays the map view for your personal vibes.
    MapViewActivity
    Placeholder activity for where the map fragment is displayed.
    MyVibesActivity
    This Activity displays the screen for a user to view a list of their vibe event history, sorted by date and time in reverse chronological order
    MyVibesAdapter
    MyVibesAdapter is a CustomList used for the ListAdapter in the main activity that serves as the list for storing vibe events
    VibeEvent
    A class that implements Serializable and keeps track of vibe events.
    VibeEventTest  
    VibeFactory
    A factory class that generates instances of different implementations of the Vibe interface depending on the user selected implementation.
    VibeFactoryTest  
    ViewProfileActivity
    This activity still does nothing but will be fixed later
    ViewVibeActivity
    This Activity displays the screen for a vibe event and all its available details
